# Git commits

**Repositorio:** raíz de `jammer-warriors/` (`.git` en la raíz del proyecto).

When creating or amending commits on behalf of the user:

- **Never** add `Co-authored-by:`, `Signed-off-by:` for Cursor, Claude, or any AI/IDE co-author line unless the user explicitly asks for it.
- The commit message must contain only what the user requested (Conventional Commits subject/body, etc.).
- **Cursor injects** `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` after `git commit` and `git commit --amend` (not a repo hook). Rules alone cannot prevent it; the agent must strip it before push.

## Preferred: `git commit-tree` (evita co-autor Cursor)

```bash
git add <paths>
cat > /tmp/commit-msg.txt <<'EOF'
feat(shop): short subject in English

EOF
TREE=$(git write-tree)
PARENT=$(git rev-parse HEAD)
NEW=$(git commit-tree "$TREE" -p "$PARENT" -F /tmp/commit-msg.txt)
git reset --hard "$NEW"
git log -1 --format=%B   # must NOT contain Co-authored-by
```

## Reescribir historial sin co-autor (varios commits)

Rebuild oldest → newest:

```bash
PARENT=""
for COMMIT in $(git log --reverse --format=%H); do
  TREE=$(git rev-parse "${COMMIT}^{tree}")
  git log -1 --format=%B "$COMMIT" | sed '/^Co-authored-by:/d' > /tmp/msg.txt
  if [ -z "$PARENT" ]; then
    NEW=$(git commit-tree "$TREE" -F /tmp/msg.txt)
  else
    NEW=$(git commit-tree "$TREE" -p "$PARENT" -F /tmp/msg.txt)
  fi
  PARENT=$NEW
done
git reset --hard "$PARENT"
```

Verify: `git log --format=%B | rg Co-authored` (expect no matches).

## If `git commit` was used anyway

- `git commit --amend -F msg.txt` is **not enough** in Cursor (trailer re-injected).
- Rewrite the last commit only:

```bash
TREE=$(git rev-parse 'HEAD^{tree}')
PARENT=$(git rev-parse 'HEAD^')
NEW=$(git commit-tree "$TREE" -p "$PARENT" -F /tmp/commit-msg.txt)
git reset --hard "$NEW"
```

